				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As I am planning to take a force via a bridge, this is a wonderful thread indeed!  However, at this point, I have two questions.  The first deals with the followed post by daetien above:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">one note about drakes. 
<br />

<br />
if you have a large mage force, you can just target a drake, pick a moment and sick all the pets in together at once. as long as you don't cast directly on the drake others will not add. 
<br />

<br />
HOWEVER- DO NOT USE EPIC PET while doing this technique. the epic has some kind of ae taunt and other drakes WILL aggro on the epic pet and once it is dead will summon the owner and kill him/her.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This seemed rather significant information, making the drake encounter much less dangerous, yet no one commented on it later.  Can anyone confirm this?  And if true, what sort of group would you deem sufficient to do the job (number of magi and pet levels)?
<br />

<br />
Second, in every thread on the 7th Isle that I have read, the drakes are attacked first.  Since they are non-aggro, could they not be taken last?  Would there be any advantage to doing so?  Probably not, even on the break-in day of the event.  (After that, you should be able to pull singles as they pop all over the island making it irrelevant.)  I ask, however, simply because I want to cover all of my bases during the planning stage.  [As for the days following the break-in, what is the respawn time?  I have heard it to be a solid 24 hours, making timing from then on easy.  However, I have also read it to be varied from 22-24 hours.  While a relatively tight window, it does make the following days more interesting.  Confirmation would be most welcome.]
<br />

<br />
As always, thanks to those of you who help to make this magician’s time in Norrath more fun by sharing your knowledge!  Safe hunting to you.
<br />

<br />
[Edit: I also wanted to confirm one final thing.  When the camp is over and you want to move everyone out of the Plane of Sky, people can simply walk over the edge, correct?  This will drop them safely into the water near the dock in East Freeport, right?  Thanks again.]</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
