			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just wanted to post my experience from spending this past long weeking in the plane of sky.
<br />

<br />
First off, we used a bridge to get to the 7th island on Friday night.  We had endless trouble with seemingly random aggro, random death touches from the sphinx etc., until we noticed that an azarack was pathing over the drake island.  This is likely the problem others have noted with being unable to get past azarack island.
<br />

<br />
For those that are unaware, azaracks are aggressive.  The problem was, this particular azarack had no way to path to us on island 7, so it would gain aggro on one of us (usually the puller) and then on it's next pass would transfer that aggro to the sphinxes who would start death touching.
<br />

<br />
After much frustration, we managed to kill off the azarack (just kept sending in the pets when it came by, and eventually it stopped warping away and just died).  From that point on, killing the drakes was a piece of cake.  We could easily pull most of the drakes solo, and even when we got two windrider drakes we were able to chain-cast pets to kill them both off.  Expect the 'puller' to die lots though - the drakes have a tendency to stun the pet then go and kill its owner.
<br />

<br />
We pulled the undine spirits before going after the sphinxes.  To do this, the puller had a corpse and got a low-level rez on it.  He'd then head in, and pull out the undines and use the rez as a feign-death to clear aggro.  We'd then send in the pets to tag the last few undines before they went back home.  Usually you'd get 2-3 at a time this way.  Just concentrate on one of them and nuke it to death quickly (they aren't very resistant).
<br />

<br />
The sphinxes were easy too, just a matter of killing them quickly.  Most sphinxes were killed before they got a chance to get a second death touch in.  I'd often suck up the death touch by starting the fight with a Sirocco.  That way, even though I'm dead from the death touch, I still get my second wave to hit.
<br />

<br />
One the first night we had 11 mages (5 of them level 61+) and an epic cleric there.  The raid went very smoothly (other than the azarack problem) and we had 4 crowns drop (from a heartsbane drake, a windrider drake, and 2x a greater sphinx).
<br />

<br />
The second night we lost some of the mages, and had a raid force of 8 mages (3 of them level 61+) and one mostly camped out, non-epic, 90% rez cleric.  We cleared the entire island with that force too, although the undine spirits caused us a great deal more trouble.  3 spirits at a time was too much and wiped the raid force, leading to a very long CR period.  Only 1 crown dropped that night (from a greater sphinx).
<br />

<br />
The third night we were down to 6 mages (levels 56, 57, 57, 60, 62, 62) along with a camped out epic cleric.  We were actually able to kill several heartsbane drakes with just the 4 of us &lt;lvl 61, but it became a lot easier once the level 62 mages logged in.  We didn't clear the entire island this time, but we did clear most of the drakes - including several windriders.  Three crowns dropped and that was all that we needed so we left a that point with everyone quite happy with the experience (although quite tired from the several late nights in a row for many of us).
<br />

<br />
So in summary:
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Night 1</span>:  11 mages + epic cleric.  Island cleared.  <span style="font-weight: bold">4 crowns</span> (heartsbane drake, windrider drake, sphinx x 2).
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Night 2</span>:  8 mages + non-epic cleric.  Island cleared.  <span style="font-weight: bold">1 crown</span> (sphinx).
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Night 3</span>:  6 mages + epic cleric.  Drakes mostly cleared.  <span style="font-weight: bold">3 crowns</span> (hearstbane drake x 2, fatestealer drake).
<br />

<br />
P.S.  We did try at one point to just send in the pets on a drake, but the other drakes DID add, despite the fact that there was no epic pet in use.  So I don't know how daetien of rallos managed to do it, but we were not able to kill drakes solo that way.  We needed to pull them out of the congo line to a safe distance away.<br />_________________<br />Master Belthil Telperion
<br />
57 Magician, Erollisi Marr</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
